    • Constructor Detail

      • FloatInterval

        public FloatInterval(FloatInterval.ConstructorType constructorType,
             float val1,
             float val2)
        This constructor takes a type argument as well as two values to construct the interval.
        Parameters:
        constructorType - The type of constructor to use either START_AND_END or RANGE_AND_CENTER.
        val1 - When the constructor type is START_AND_END then this is the start of the interval. When the constructor type is RANGE_AND_CENTER then this is the range of the interval.
        val2 - When the constructor type is START_AND_END then this is the end of the interval. When the constructor type is RANGE_AND_CENTER then this is the center of the interval.

      • truncate

        public float truncate(float value)
        Truncates the given value into a value that is within the interval. For example if the given value is greater than the interval, then the end of the interval is returned. If the given value is less than the interval then the start of the interval is returned.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to truncate.
        Returns:
        The truncated value.
